==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wail
<hw>Wail</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>val</ets> choice, <ets>velja</ets> to choose, akin to Goth.
<ets>waljan</ets>, G. <ets>w⟦aum⟧hlen</ets>.]</ety> <def>To choose; to
select.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Wailed</xex> wine and
meats.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Henryson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wail</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wail
<hw>Wail</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Wailed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Wailing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>wailen</ets>,
<ets>weilen</ets>, probably fr. Icel. <ets>v⟦ae⟧la</ets>; cf. Icel.
<ets>v⟦ae⟧</ets>, <ets>vei</ets>, woe, and E. <ets>wayment</ets>, also
OE. <ets>wai</ets>, <ets>wei</ets>, woe. Cf. <er>Woe</er>.]</ety>
<def>To lament; to bewail; to grieve over; <as>as, to <ex>wail</ex>
one's death</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wail</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wail
<hw>Wail</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To express sorrow audibly; to make
mournful outcry; to weep.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Therefore I will <qex>wail</qex> and howl.</q> <rj><au>Micah i.
8.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wail</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Wail
<hw>Wail</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Loud weeping; violent lamentation;
wailing.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>wail</xex> of the forest.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wailer</ent>⟦br⟧
